<br>
youre right, but this phenomena is explained by rates of aggro decay. for any of you who have done even rudimentary calculus, you can look at aggro as first, for each person, creating 2 rates. one a rate of decay, based upon distance from the mob, two, a rate of increase based upon damage per time. Then you have to do a model using X axis as time with yourself compared to the main tank. If ever you line goes above the tanks, you get aggro.<br>
<br>
I dont know the exact numbers, but maybe if im bored enough ill throw together some symbolic equations and GRAPHS to show how it works.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/4/03 8:58:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26371.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> aggro decay</span><hr size=1> aggro has been observed to decay at intervals. I've noticed this to be about 30 seconds. The greatest likelyhood(imo) for the decay is that everyone's hate is reduced to a certain percentage of what it was prior... mobs can also totally forget you during a fight, theres some ways to achieve that intentionally, some used to just occur unintentionally, and still does. while I'm not sure about the 'intervals', it seems close to 30 seconds.<br>
<br>
this, I think, is why it's best to nuke as soon as possible. free concussions, basically. the fast damage thing is correct as SOS goes. Any wizard who knows how to play the class can manage the SOS aggro, myself and many others have for a very long time. there's some exceptions, such as mem blurring junk. naturally a draught just makes the aggro a whole lot slower than a SOS does.<br>
