<br>
as for draughts, in a certain fight i found i needed 1 1/2 aconcs per sos, and could draught 5x per aconc. if I'm not missing anything, SOS is 40% hasted by me, draughts 30% hasted, and with an 18% crit rate and 20% focus(I use more, though), 128.5% is the dmg boost.<br>
<br>
SOS: (2740)(1.285) = 3521dmg, 7.05s per<br>
Draughts: (950)(1.285) = 1221 4.35s per<br>
aconc: no damage, 4.25s per<br>
<br>
SOS 3512dmg 7.05s<br>
aconc 4.25s<br>
aconc 4.25s<br>
SOS 3512dmg 7.05s<br>
aconc 4.25s<br>
26.85s 7042dmg 262dps<br>
<br>
Draughts 5x- 6015dmg 21.75s<br>
aconc- 4.25s<br>
6015dmg 26s 231dps<br>
<br>
I shall now take the above method and make a new unit for all of this. the hypothetical 'aggro unit'. I'll give a conc 1 aggro unit per hate removed, and a DD above 1 aggro per dmg it does, reducable by SCS. going a little above this for draughts was a summon, a little below for concs was a summon... they aggrod similarly, i found. additionally, lag and slowness effects draughts more greatly than a sos(for do do the same dmg, you must whack the button three times as much about). on the other hand, a draught is less effected by spell interrupts, as there's the longer cast time of sos, and much of the dps is shouldered off into the standard recast time(which doesnt occur when interrupted).<br>
<br>
as for tank downs, the main tank always has more aggro by a bit than the next tank on the list. after all, the mob would select a new main tank if this were not so. they also get procs off of ripostes. if you can expect the infamous healer sucking at 4am(MT down to 1k hitter trash! oops), or something that can do 12k tank life in a round or such then you shall need to know one obvious truth... the next tank in line has a bit less aggro than the former tank, and if you're between their aggros, then you're splatting. just having a high amount of aggro in general will get you summoned. comapred to draughts? no, I should say that they are no different given concussions and the ability to sit on your ass and do nothing- ie no more aggro.<br>
<br>
